  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.1.0 (0b6b202 2022-02-04T16:41:12.396200+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge remove <dependency>\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (M1)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nthe remove function executes the git command \"git checkout -- .\" which has the effect of erasing any unstaged changes in the working tree.  I can fix this but not sure which direction to go.\r\n\r\nSee offending code here:\r\nhttps://github.com/gakonst/foundry/blob/master/cli/src/forge.rs#L120\r\n\r\n1. This is intended behavior and I can add a prompt to the command \"Make sure no uncommitted changes are present\"\r\n\r\n2. This is unintended and I can remove the last command (it doesn't seem necessary)",
